content:
Automated prediction writeback saves numeric prediction scores to a field in a Salesforce object. Using this feature requires deploying a model that outputs a numerical prediction or score and mapping all model fields back to Salesforce fields.

In Model Manager, open a prediction definition and click Enable next to Automated Prediction Writeback. Select one of the following options:

* Create a prediction field: Have Einstein create the prediction field using the prediction field label you specify.
* Use an existing prediction field: Store prediction results in an existing prediction field.
* Don't store predictions: Don't store the prediction value in a prediction field, or store results in a custom field that you configure later.

Click Save. To configure performance alerts, click Save and Next, then proceed to Configure Model Quality Notifications.
title: Configure Automated Prediction Writeback in Salesforce
